I’ve read the **Charter of Pragmatic Resilience (v4.0)** carefully. It is, I suspect, the most comprehensive attempt to align ethics with ecology in a single document I have seen. I agree with your central premise: the current path is unsustainable. We need a new moral framework.

However, as an economist who argues that **long-term economic growth is the single most reliable path to human flourishing**, I believe your framework suffers from a specific set of structural flaws that could actually undermine the very resilience you seek to build.

