rces whenever the planetary‑boundary thresholds are threatened, rather than a static set of principles that can be ignored when powerful actors have the power to do so.  In short, I now see the charter as a *framework of hard constraints, transparent accounting and cultural‑rights safeguards* that must be built into the very architecture of global governance if it is ever to protect both sentient beings and the planet, rather than a set of lofty ideals that can be politely ignored.

