### Summary of the Blind Spots
If you were to argue *against* this framework, your strongest point would be that it is **too clean**. It envisions a world of high-functioning, empathetic, evidence-based stewards. 

It leaves out the **Shadow**: the irrationality, the greed, the tribalism, and the chaotic spark of the individual ego. It builds a cathedral of reason and empathy, but it may have underestimated the depth of the wilderness within the human psyche.

